@node Usage

                     Using FastPAR V1.0
                     ==================


FastPAR requires Kickstart V37 (2.04) or later.

Before  you  can  use  FastPAR,  you have to install it.
Copy FastPAR-Handler to your L: directory.

If  you  are  running  V37  (OS2.04/2.05), add the following
lines to your devs:MountList file:

FastPAR:     Handler = L:FastPAR-Handler
             Priority = 5
             Stacksize = 4000
             GlobVec = -1
#

You may then make FastPAR: available by issuing the command
"Mount FastPAR:"; either by using a Shell or by putting it
into your s:User-Startup file.

If  you  are using V38 (OS2.1) or later versions of AmigaOS,
simply  drag  the  FastPAR  icon into Devs:DOSDrivers if you
want  FastPAR:  to be mounted every time you boot; or put it
anywhere   else   if   you   want   to  mount  FastPAR:   by
double-clicking its icon.

Once  FastPAR:  has been mounted, it can used like any other
DOS-Device.   Simply  send your data to FastPAR:  instead of
PAR:   For  example,  to  use  FastPAR  with PasTeX by Georg
Heßmann you can use the command

   dviprint File.dvi OutTo=FastPAR:

and  you  will  finally  be able to go on working while your
dvi-file is printing.


FastPAR supports the ACTION_DIE packet, so you can remove it
from  memory if you don't need it anymore.

@endnode

